  'banff-geocaching': `
<p>Geocaching in Banff National Park adds an extra layer of adventure to any hike or walk. The treasure-hunting game — using GPS coordinates to find hidden containers — has a thriving community in the Canadian Rockies, with dozens of approved caches hidden along trails, in towns, and at scenic viewpoints throughout the park.</p>

