  'banff-cross-country-skiing': `
<p>Cross-country skiing in Banff National Park is one of winter's great pleasures — gliding through snow-covered forests, along frozen rivers, and past mountain panoramas on groomed trails that range from gentle beginner loops to challenging backcountry routes. It's quieter, cheaper, and more accessible than downhill skiing, and Banff has some of the best Nordic skiing in Canada.</p>

